issue.body:
[This example](http://react-day-picker.js.org/examples/selecting-range-mouse-enter.html) (see discussion in #202) has some logic that could be extracted in an external component.

Inspired by the [date picker](http://airbnb.io/react-dates/?selectedKind=DateRangePicker&selectedStory=with%20some%20blocked%20dates&full=0&down=1&left=1&panelRight=0) from Airbnb, a possible API would be:

```jsx
import { DayRangePicker } from 'react-day-picker;

<DayRangePicker
  minimumDays={ 3 }
  onRangeSelect={ (range, days) => handleRangeSelect(range) }
/>
```

Wondering if the component could even allow multiple ranges...

comment.body:
Hey @jordanoverbye thanks for you PR. We already planned updates to the aria label in #1550. In your case, you should use the [labels](https://react-day-picker.js.org/api/types/Labels) prop:

https://codesandbox.io/s/react-daypicker-forked-8sme19?file=/src/App.tsx

```tsx
import { DayLabel, DayPicker } from 'react-day-picker';
const labelDay: DayLabel = (day, activeModifiers, options): string => {
   return format(day, 'do MMMM yyyy (EEEE)', options);
 };
function MyApp() {
  return <DayPicker labels={{ labelDay }} />;
}
```

